What's the purpose of

 RETURN;

in sixth line? I removed this and it still work (probably) correctly.

The part about rules is incorrect as of 2020. Use

 `    "rules": {
        "react/prop-types": 0
    }
`

I have tested the above code and also some other asynchronous theories and the problem still occurs.

I was performing some tests and discovered something... The following code works:

`app.use(express.static(__dirname + "/../../../np-site/themes/default/client/css"));`

but when it's wrapped in a Mongoose server call:

`App.find(function (err, appSettings) {
        app.use(express.static(__dirname + "/../../../np-site/themes/default/client/css"));
    });`

It doesn't work. I must be missing something.

